FBIS4-16383 "drsov073_a_94036" FBIS-SOV-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS 5-Km Zone Set Up Along Russian-Chinese Border 5-Km Zone Set Up Along Russian-Chinese Border LD1404171694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1055 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404171694 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] A five-kilometer zone with a special entry regime will pass along the Russian-Chinese border on the territory of the Jewish autonomous region along the Russian bank of the Amur River. From now on economic, and other activities in the border zone will be done only with the consent of border-guard troops. The entry and exit of the zone will only be allowed when residence permits are shown. Residents of other territories will have to get special documents permitting their entry. Foreigners are to be registered at local police stations. The toughened measures are linked with frequent cases of border violations and the deterioration of the criminal situation in the border zone.
